# FHEVM / Zama Protocol — Windsurf rules

This project builds confidential smart contracts with the Zama Protocol (FHEVM). Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for the full task routing table and critical rules. Everything below is a summary; `AGENTS.md` and the `references/` directory are authoritative.

## Critical rules — enforce on every FHEVM code change

1. Never use `if` / `require` on an encrypted value. Use `FHE.select(cond, a, b)`.
2. After writing a ciphertext to storage, always call `FHE.allowThis(ct)`. This is mandatory.
3. When a user should be able to decrypt a ciphertext client-side, always call `FHE.allow(ct, userAddress)`.
4. `view` functions return handles (`bytes32`), not plaintexts. Decryption is async.
5. Unwrap every encrypted input with `FHE.fromExternal(handle, inputProof)` before use.
6. `FHE.div` / `FHE.rem` require a plaintext RHS.
7. Inherit `ZamaEthereumConfig` in every FHE contract (one Solidity base — handles mainnet, Sepolia, localhost automatically).
8. Use `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` — not `fhevmjs`.
9. In tests, use `@fhevm/hardhat-plugin` helpers. Never mock FHE.
10. Public decryption handle order must match exactly between contract and client.
11. Loop bounds must be plaintext.
12. User decryption request total ≤ 2048 bits.

